Aaiye isko 4 aasan hisso mein tod kar samajhte hain.

1. Yeh saare Arguments kisko bheje ja rahe hain?
Yeh saare ke saare <Arg> (Arguments) Provisioning Approval Subprocess ko bheje ja rahe hain.

Agar aap step ke bottom mein dekhenge, toh wahan yeh code likha hai:

XML
<WorkflowRef>
  <Reference class="sailpoint.object.Workflow" name="Provisioning Approval Subprocess"/>
</WorkflowRef>
Iska matlab hai ki SailPoint is step par aakar ek Child Workflow (Subprocess) ko chalu kar raha hai jiska naam "Provisioning Approval Subprocess" hai. Yeh saare arguments isi child workflow ko chalne ke liye diye ja rahe hain.

2. In saare Arguments ko Value kaun de raha hai?
In arguments ko value dene ke do alag-alag tarike use ho rahe hain:

Master Variables (value="ref:..."): Jinke aage ref: laga hai (jaise ref:identityName, ref:plan), unhe value Main Workflow ke Master Variables se mil rahi hai jo pichle steps mein save hui thi.

Inbuilt Script (value="script:..."): Kuch arguments (jaise clearApprovalDecisions) ko value unke andar turant chalne wali ek choti si logical script se mil rahi hai.

Khaali/Blank Arguments: Jin arguments ke aage koi value="..." nahi likha hai (jaise approvingIdentities ya workItemMaxReminders), unhe shuruat mein koi value nahi di ja rahi hai (wo khali hain), ya fir unki value configForm ke settings page se automatic uthakar pass kar di jayegi.

3. Yeh saare Arguments kya hain aur kya karte hain?
Inhe aasan shabdo mein samajhne ke liye hum categories mein baant lete hain:

A. Approval Model aur Scheme (Approval ka Tarika)
approvalMode: Yeh batata hai ki approvals kaise chalenge—Serial (ek ke baad ek) ya Parallel (sabko ek sath).

approvalScheme: Yeh batata hai ki approver kaun hoga (jaise manager, owner, ya securityOfficer).

approvalSet & approvalSplitPoint: Isme un saari items ki list hoti hai jinhe approve karna hai, aur split point unhe alag-alag tukdo mein todta hai.

fallbackApprover: Agar system ko asli approver (jaise user ka manager) nahi mila, toh backup ke taur par approval kiske paas jayega.

clearApprovalDecisions: Ek check lagata hai ki agar plan pehle split ho chuka hai, toh purane decisions ko clear karke naye sire se approval start kiya jaye.

B. Identity aur Target Information (Kiska access hai)
identityName & identityDisplayName: Jis employee ke liye access manga gaya hai, uska unique username aur uska asli naam.

launcher: Jisne yeh request shuru ki hai (jaise koi HR, Manager ya user khud).

identityRequestId: Is request ka unique tracking ID number.

plan & project: Kya access manga gaya hai uska blueprint (Plan) aur compiled project.

C. Notification aur Templates (Email aur Signature)
managerEmailTemplate / ownerEmailTemplate / securityOfficerEmailTemplate: Jab Manager, Application Owner ya Security Officer ke paas approval jayega, toh unhe jo email notification dikhega uska design/template kya hoga.

managerElectronicSignature...: Kya manager ko approve karte waqt apna password daal kar digital sign karna compulsory hai ya nahi.

D. Reminders aur Escalation (Ander ka intezaam)
workItemReminderTemplate & workItemHoursBetweenReminders: Approver ko bheje jaane wale reminder email ka template, aur kitne ghanton ke baad baar-baar reminder bhejna hai.

workItemMaxReminders: Ek approver ko maximum kitne reminder bheje ja sakte hain.

workItemEscalationTemplate & workItemEscalationRule: Agar manager fix time tak approve na kare, toh request aage kiske paas bhejni (escalate karni) hai aur uska rule kya hoga.

