</sailpoint> abb list de ki koun kisse value deta hai jiska intializer nahi hai

Aapne jo "Approve and Provision Subprocess" ka XML code diya hai, isme se un saare variables ki list niche di gayi hai jinka koi initializer nahi hai.

Yeh subprocess jab main workflow ke zariye call kiya jata hai, toh SailPoint engine parde ke peeche in variables ko values assign karta hai. Niche di gayi table se aapko ek-ek variable ka exact source samajh aa jayega:

Variables jinka Initializer nahi hai (Value Sources)
Variable Name	Isko Value Kaun Deta Hai? (Exact Source)	Kab aur Kaise Milti Hai Value?
identityName	Parent/Main Workflow	Jab main workflow is subprocess ko start karta hai, toh woh target user ka exact ID (identityName) isme pass karta hai.
plan	Parent/Main Workflow	Jo original ProvisioningPlan access request ke time bana tha, woh main workflow isko as an input saunp deta hai.
flow	Parent/Main Workflow	Main workflow pehle se jaanta hai ki kaun sa flow chal raha hai (AccountsRequest, EntitlementsRequest, ya RolesRequest), wahi value yahan bhej di jaati hai.
batchRequestItemId	Batch Excel/CSV File Process	Agar yeh request kisi batch file ke zariye bulk mein aayi hai, toh batch engine us individual row ki unique ID isme daalta hai. Normal request mein yeh null rehta hai.
securityOfficerEmailTemplate	Business Process Configuration (UI)	Agar system setting mein Security Officer ke liye koi custom email template select kiya gaya hai toh wahan se milti hai, warna yeh system default uthata hai.
securityOfficerName	System Configuration / UI Settings	Agar company ke global settings mein kisi standard Security Officer ka naam map kiya gaya hai, toh SailPoint wahan se uthakar isme bhejta hai.
approvalAssignmentRule	Business Process Configuration (UI)	Agar admin ne approval ke dynamic assignment ke liye koi custom Rule select kiya hai, toh us Rule ka naam yahan pass hota hai.
formTemplate	Provision Step ya UI Defaults	Is variable ko value niche chalne wala Provision step khud "Identity Update" ke roop mein aage pass kar deta hai. Shuruat mein yeh blank rehta hai.
manualActionsEmailTemplate	Provision Step ya UI Defaults	formTemplate ki tarah, ise bhi Provision step ke andar "Pending Manual Changes" ki value milti hai.
approvalSplitPoint	Parent/Main Workflow	Main workflow jab pooray plan ko todta hai (Split karta hai), toh woh current split configuration is variable ko pass karta hai.
approvingIdentities	Approval Step Calculation	Shuruat mein yeh khali hota hai. Approve step chalne par SailPoint ka engine dynamic tarike se dhoondhta hai ki approver kaun hai, aur uski ID isme bhar deta hai.
Kuch Khaas Variables Jo Shuru Mein Khaali Hain Par Beech Mein Bharte Hain:
In variables ka bhi koi initializer nahi hai, kyunki inka kaam hi pichle steps ke results ko store karna hai:

project: Iska apna koi initializer nahi hai kyunki "Compile Project" step chalne par resultVariable="project" ke zariye SailPoint ka core engine isme compiled project ki value daalta hai.

approvalSet: Iska bhi koi initializer nahi hai kyunki "Build Approval Set" step chalne par resultVariable="approvalSet" ke zariye isme line items ki value store hoti hai.

policyViolations: Shuruat mein poora khali rehta hai. Agar main workflow ne pehle se koi policy violation scan ki hui hai, toh woh list isme bhej di jaati hai taaki approver ko warning dikhe.

identityRequestId: Main workflow isme ticket id (jaise 000000123) bhejta hai, taaki is pooray subprocess ki tracking us main ticket se judi rahe.

workItemComments: Shuru mein khali hota hai, par jaise hi koi approver comment likhta hai, child subprocess is variable ko upar ki taraf update kar deta hai.

sare variables me value koun deta hai list line by line

Aapke Approve and Provision Subprocess workflow ke andar jitne bhi variables define hain (chahe unka initializer ho ya na ho), un sabko value kaun, kab aur kaise deta hai, iski line-by-line poori list niche di gayi hai:

1. identityName
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Parent (Main) Workflow

Kaise/Kab: Jab main workflow is subprocess ko start karta hai, toh jis user ke liye request bani hai uska unique username/ID isme bhej deta hai.

2. endOnManualWorkItems
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Initializer (false) aur Admin UI Settings

Kaise/Kab: Shuruat mein iski value false set hoti hai. Agar Admin ne SailPoint ke configuration page par is setting ko change kiya hai, toh wahan se nayi value milti hai.

3. endOnProvisioningForms
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Initializer (false) aur Admin UI Settings

Kaise/Kab: Bilkul upar wale variable ki tarah, shuru mein false rehta hai aur zaroorat padne par Admin UI se iski value badli jaati hai.

4. identityDisplayName
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Script

Kaise/Kab: Yeh variable chalte hi ek chota sa code run karta hai. Agar system ke paas display name pehle se hai, toh wahi rakh leta hai, nahi toh resolveDisplayName(identityName) function ko call karke user ka asli naam database se nikal leta hai.

5. plan
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Parent (Main) Workflow

Kaise/Kab: Jo original raw request (blueprint) bani thi, use Main Workflow is variable ke andar daal kar subprocess ko saunp deta hai.

6. flow
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Parent (Main) Workflow / SailPoint UI Context

Kaise/Kab: Main workflow shuruat mein hi isme batata hai ki user kya kaam kar raha hai (AccountsRequest, EntitlementsRequest, ya RolesRequest).

7. optimisticProvisioning
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Initializer (false) aur Admin UI Settings

Kaise/Kab: Default value false hoti hai. Agar admin chahta hai ki badlav turant user ke account par dikhein, toh woh UI se ise true kar deta hai.

8. foregroundProvisioning
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Initializer (true) aur Admin UI Settings

Kaise/Kab: Shuruat mein true rehta hai taaki testing/demo ke waqt provisioning turant screen ke samne ho jaye. Ise bhi UI se change kiya ja sakta hai.

9. batchRequestItemId
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Batch Excel/CSV File Process

Kaise/Kab: Agar request bulk file ke zariye aayi hai, toh batch processing engine us individual line ki ID isme bhejta hai. Normal single request mein yeh hamesha khali (null) rehta hai.

10. userEmailTemplate
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Initializer ("LCM User Notification")

Kaise/Kab: Workflow shuru hote hi isme standard email template ka naam set ho jata hai, jiska use user ko mail bhejne ke liye hota hai.

11. requesterEmailTemplate
Value Kaun Deta Hai: Inbuilt Initializer ("LCM Requester Notification")

Kaise/Kab: Workflow shuru hote hi isme requester (request dalne wale) ke email template ka naam set ho jata hai.

12. managerEmailTemplate
