Aaiye in dono cheezon ko ekdam aamne-saamne rakh kar samajhte hain ki inka asli maqsad kya hai aur yeh milkar kya kaam karte hain.

1. ticketManagementApplication kyun use hota hai? (The "Why")
Iska use SailPoint ko company ke doosre IT ticketing systems (jaise ServiceNow ya Jira) se jodne ke liye kiya jata hai.

Kyun zaroori hai?
Badi companies mein audit aur tracking ke liye ek central ticketing tool hota hai (aamtaur par ServiceNow). Agar koi employee access maangta hai, toh company chahti hai ki uska ek official ticket record ServiceNow mein bhi banna chahiye.

Iska kaam: Yeh variable SailPoint ko batata hai ki hume kis ticketing app (e.g., "ServiceNow") ke andar jaakar badlav karne hain.

Fayda: Agar yeh variable set hai, toh SailPoint automatic us system se baat karega. Agar company koi external ticketing tool use nahi karti, toh is variable ko null (khali) chhod diya jata hai, aur SailPoint bina kisi ticket ke seedhe apna kaam karta hai.

2. action="postApproval" kya hai aur kya karta hai? (The "What")
Yeh ek Command/Signal (Ishara) hai jo Manage Ticket subprocess ko batata hai ki ticket ke sath is samay kya karna hai.

Yeh kya karta hai?
Ek ticket ke alag-alag phases hote hain: Open hona → Manager Approval milna → Access milna (Close hona).

postApproval ka matlab hai: "Manager ne SailPoint mein request ko 'Approve' kar diya hai."

Asli Action: Jaise ہی Manage Ticket ko yeh postApproval ka signal milta hai, woh ServiceNow/Jira ke paas jata hai aur wahan chal rahe ticket ka status badal kar "Approved" ya "Work In Progress" set kar deta hai, aur sath hi agar manager ne koi comments likhe hain, toh unhe ticket ke notes mein update kar deta hai.

Ek Simple Kissa (Dono ka तालमेल)
Maan lijiye aapne bank mein ek Loan Request dali. Bank ka ek main system hai (SailPoint) aur ek central file cabinet hai (ServiceNow).

Manager ne SailPoint par aapka loan Approve kar diya.

Tabhi yeh step trigger hota hai. Yeh check karta hai ki file cabinet (ticketManagementApplication="ServiceNow") maujood hai ya nahi.

Maujood hai, toh SailPoint ek employee ko bolta hai: "Jaao aur us file cabinet mein jo ticket chal raha hai, uspar 'Post Approval' (action="postApproval") ka thappa (stamp) laga do aur likh do ki Manager ne haan bol diya hai, taaki aage cash counter wale apna kaam shuru kar sakein."

agar pre approval hota toh

Agar preApproval hota, toh iska matlab hota "Approval hone se pehle" (Before Approval).

Agar code mein action="preApproval" likha hota, toh yeh step Approve wale step se pehle chalta. Aaiye dekhte hain ki tab yeh kya kaam karta:

1. Tab yeh kya karta? (The Action)
Jaise hi koi employee access ke liye request submit karta, SailPoint manager ke paas approval bhejane se bhi pehle ServiceNow/Jira ke paas jata.

Asli Kaam: Yeh ServiceNow mein ek ekdam Naya Ticket Paida (Create/Open) karta.

Ticket Status: Us ticket ka status setting ke mutabik "New" ya "Submitted" ya "Pending Approval" set kar deta.

Tracking: ServiceNow se jo Naya Ticket Number milta (jaise REQ00123), use laakar SailPoint ke database mein save kar deta taaki dono system aapas mein jud sakein.

2. Dono mein saaf antar (Pre vs Post):
preApproval (Shuruat mein): External ticketing system ko batata hai ki "Ek nayi request aayi hai, iska ek naya ticket kholo (Open)."

postApproval (Beech mein): Us purane khule hue ticket ko update karta hai ki "Manager ne request ko approve kar diya hai, ab iska status badal kar Approved/In Progress kar do."

Aapke pooray Workflow ke hisab se samajhiye:
Aapke is subprocess ke andar ticket update ka poora safar aise chalta agar shuruat se ticket management chal raha hota:

