Aaiye in teeno cheezon ko ekdam aasan language mein samajhte hain ki ek pure custom workflow mein inka kya matlab hota hai:

1. Workflow Kya Hai? (Asli Matlab)
SailPoint mein Workflow ek automatic "Flowchart" ya "Safar" hai jo yeh tay karta hai ki koi bhi request shuru hone se lekar khatam hone tak kis-kis raste se guzregi.

Aasan Example: Jaise office mein leave (chutti) lene ka ek fixed niyam hota hai: Aapne apply kiya → Manager ke paas mail gaya → Manager ne haan bola → HR system mein entry hui → Aapko notification aaya.

SailPoint ke andar isi poore niyam (business process) ko auto-pilot par chalane ke liye hum XML code mein ek Workflow likh dete hain. Yeh automatic ek step se dusre step par request ko lekar jata hai.

2. <Step ... approvalOwner="ref:managerName">
Yeh line SailPoint ko batati hai ki is step par jo approval ka ticket banega, uska asli malik (owner) kaun hoga aur kiski screen par dikhega.

approvalOwner: Iska matlab hai ki jab tak is step par koi insaan "Approve" ya "Reject" nahi karega, workflow aage nahi badhega. Yeh ek security check-post hai.

ref:managerName: Yahan ref: ka matlab hai Reference (ishara). Yeh variable pichle step se employee ke manager ka naam (jaise john.doe) dhoodh kar laya hai.

Asli Kaam: SailPoint is line ko padhte hi us manager ke dashboard par ek action item bhej dega. Manager jab subah apna SailPoint kholega, toh use samne ek ticket dikhega kyunki woh us ticket ka approvalOwner hai.

3.  ke andar Approve aur Reject
Yeh manager ko dikhne wale custom form ke andar ka ek Dropdown Menu (Drop-down Options) hai.

Asli Kaam: Jab manager ke samne approval ka screen (Form) khulega, toh wahan ek field hogi: "Do you approve this access?" Manager uspar click karega toh use sirf do hi options dikhein iske liye humne  (allowed choices) set kar di hain:

Approve (Haan)

Reject (Naa)

Iske alawa manager wahan apni marzi se kuch aur ulta-seedha text type nahi kar sakta. Jo option woh select karega, wahi value approvalDecision naam ke variable mein save ho jayegi.

4. ...Aur Kya? (Iske aage kya hota hai?)
Jaise hi manager in dono mein se ek choice select karke "Submit Decision" button dabata hai, workflow ka agla step chalta hai jo is decision ko check karta hai:

Agar manager ne Approve chuna: Toh workflow chala jata hai Custom Provisioning Logic par, jahan automatic Active Directory ya target application mein user ka account ban jata hai.

Agar manager ne Reject chuna: Toh transition condition use seedhe Stop step par bhej deti hai. Request wahin cancel ho jati hai, user ko koi access nahi milta, aur ServiceNow ka ticket close ho jata hai.


