aur ye form kaha upload kare:- aur ish workflow ko chalane ka koi rule bhi hai kya

Aaiye aapke in dono sawalon ka ekdam step-by-step jawab samajhte hain ki is Form aur Workflow ko SailPoint mein kahan daalna hai aur ise chalane ke liye kya niyam ya rules hote hain.

1. Yeh Form aur Workflow kahan upload karein?
SailPoint IdentityIQ (IIQ) mein kisi bhi XML file (chahe woh Form ho, Workflow ho, ya Rule) ko upload karne ka ek hi standard tarika hota hai, jise hum "Import" bolte hain.

Upload karne ka tarika (Sequence):
Pehle aap Form XML ka code ek notepad mein save karke uska naam SampleForm.xml rakh lijiye.

Phir Workflow XML ka code save karke uska naam SampleWorkflow.xml rakh lijiye.

SailPoint IIQ ke Console UI par jaaiye aur top menu mein Global Settings (Gears ka icon) par click kirdi-jiye.

Wahan dropdown mein aapko Import from File ka option milega.

Pehle Form ki XML file ko select karke Import button dabaiye, aur uske baad Workflow ki XML file ko select karke Import dabaiye.

Zaroori Baat: Hamesha pehle Form ko import karna, phir Workflow ko. Kyunki agar aapne pehle workflow import kiya, toh SailPoint validation error de dega ki "Bhai, mujhe Sample Workflow Form naam ka form database mein nahi mil raha hai!"

2. Is Workflow ko chalane ka koi Rule bhi hai kya?
Technically, is workflow ko direct chalane ke liye koi Java/BeanShell Rule nahi chahiye hota hai. Lekin isko trigger karne ke liye SailPoint ka ek niyam/setup hota hai jise hum QuickLink Configuration bolte hain.

Aapka sawal tha ki user ka ek "QuickLink hai jo workflow ko trigger karta hai". Toh use chalane ke liye parde ke peeche yeh 3 niyam (Steps) poore hone chahiye:

Niyam A: Ek QuickLink Object Hona Chahiye
Aapko SailPoint mein ek QuickLink object banana padta hai jo dashboard par ek button ke roop mein dikhega. Us QuickLink XML ke andar aapko batana padta hai ki is button ke dabte hi kaun sa workflow chalega.

Uska configuration kuch aisa dikhta hai:

XML
<QuickLink name="Dynamic Survey Button" action="workflow" category="SelfService">
  <Attributes>
    <Map>
      <!-- Yeh line aapke custom workflow ko jodti hai -->
      <entry key="workflowName" value="Sample Workflow"/> 
    </Map>
  </Attributes>
</QuickLink>
Niyam B: QuickLink Options Rule (Optional but Useful)
Agar aap chahte hain ki yeh button kis-kis employee ko dikhe (jaise sirf Managers ko dikhe, ya sirf IT team ko dikhe), toh uske liye ek QuickLink Options Rule likha jata hai. Yeh rule sirf true ya false return karta hai yeh tay karne ke liye ki dashboard par button visible hoga ya nahi.

Niyam C: Identity QuickLink Id Framework (Most Important)
Aapne user ke purane code mein dekha tha ki wahan ek variable use ho raha tha: quickLinkIdentityId.

SailPoint ka yeh niyam hai ki jab aap dashboard par kisi employee ke naam ke aage jaakar custom button dabate hain, toh SailPoint automatic us target employee ka unique ID quickLinkIdentityId naam ke variable mein generate karke is workflow ko bhej deta hai. Humne jo naya code combine kiya hai, woh isi niyam ka fayda utha kar launcher aur user ka data sahi se nikaalta hai.

Niyam C: Identity QuickLink Id Framework (Most Important)

Aapne user ke purane code mein dekha tha ki wahan ek variable use ho raha tha: quickLinkIdentityId.

SailPoint ka yeh niyam hai ki jab aap dashboard par kisi employee ke naam ke aage jaakar custom button dabate hain, toh SailPoint automatic us target employee ka unique ID quickLinkIdentityId naam ke variable mein generate karke is workflow ko bhej deta hai. teeno ka de poora xml

Aaiye ab is poore system ko aapas mein jodne ke liye Teeno Objects (QuickLink, Form, aur Workflow) ka complete XML ek sath dekhte hain.

Jab aap in teeno ko SailPoint mein daal denge, toh yeh automatic ek dusre se baat karenge: QuickLink button dikhayega aur target user ki ID (quickLinkIdentityId) pass karega → Workflow chalega → Form dynamic fields ke sath load ho jayega.

Object 1: QuickLink XML (Niyam A & C ka Setup)
Yeh XML aapke SailPoint ke dashboard par ek button banayega jiska naam hoga "Dynamic Survey Portal". Isme action="workflow" aur workflowName="Sample Workflow" set hai, jo seedhe aapke custom workflow ko trigger karega aur target identity ki ID parde ke peeche pass kar dega.

