IIQ Mein Iska Kya Fayda Hua?
No Context Break: Pure Java code ko humne Step script ke andar hi block kiya hai, jisse loop chalte waqt SailPoint ka standard API context kabhi khota nahi hai aur pure database se dynamic queries safely chalti hain.

Explicit Workflow Variables: Java script execute hote hi unhone user ka display name aur ID nikal kar direct workflow.put() kar diya hai. Isse variables pure session ke dauran memory mein bane rehte hain aur jab Email Step chalta hai, toh use variables ekdam tight aur filled milte hain!

aur koi rule wul bhi hai kya ishka

Haan bhai, SailPoint IdentityIQ (IIQ) mein is poore setup ko automatic chalane ke liye aur filters check karne ke liye ek bahut zaroori Rule lagta hai, jise hum IdentityTrigger Rule bolte hain.

Aapka workflow tab tak apne aap nahi chalega jab tak aap use batayenge nahi ki kab chalna hai. To isko auto-pilot par daalne ke liye parde ke peeche 3 main rules aur settings kaam karti hain:

1. IdentityTrigger Rule (Sabse Zaroori Rule)
Jab kisi user ka profile badalta hai, toh yeh Rule check karta hai ki kya sach mein uska Role Code ya Lifecycle State badla hai? Agar badla hota hai, toh yeh rule true return karta hai, jisse aapka workflow apne aap chal jata hai.

Aap is Trigger Rule XML ko SailPoint mein import kar sakte hain:

XML
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Rule PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Rule name="Cellphone Trigger Attribute Change Rule" type="IdentityTrigger">
  <Description>Yeh rule check karta hai ki user ka Role Code ya Lifecycle State badla hai ya nahi.</Description>
  <Source>
    <![CDATA[
    import sailpoint.object.Identity;

    boolean triggerWorkflow = false;

    // 'newIdentity' (badla hua data) aur 'oldIdentity' (purana data) SailPoint hume automatic deta hai
    if (newIdentity != null && oldIdentity != null) {
        
        // 1. Check karo kya Lifecycle State badla hai?
        String oldState = oldIdentity.getLifecycleState();
        String newState = newIdentity.getLifecycleState();
        
        // 2. Check karo kya Role Code badla hai? (Maan lijiye attribute ka naam 'roleCode' hai)
        String oldRole = (String) oldIdentity.getAttribute("roleCode");
        String newRole = (String) newIdentity.getAttribute("roleCode");

        // Agar dono mein se kuch bhi badla (change) hua hai, toh trigger ko true kar do
        if ((newState != null && !newState.equals(oldState)) || (newRole != null && !newRole.equals(oldRole))) {
            triggerWorkflow = true;
        }
    }

    return triggerWorkflow; // Agar true return hua, toh workflow trigger ho jayega
    ]]>
  </Source>
</Rule>
2. Lifecyle Event Configuration (Niyam)
Upar wale Rule aur Workflow ko aapas mein jodne ke liye SailPoint mein ek Lifecycle Event banana padta hai. Isme hum batate hain ki jab bhi koi Identity Modify (badal) ho, toh upar wala Trigger Rule chalao, aur agar rule true bole, toh humara main Workflow shuru kar do.

Uska configuration sancha (XML) aisa hota hai:

XML
<IdentityLifecycleEvent name="Company Phone Certification Event" type="Alert" lostAccess="false">
  <!-- Kaunsa workflow chalana hai -->
  <WorkflowRef name="Cellphone Certification Reminder Workflow"/>
  
  <!-- Kaunsa trigger rule check karna hai -->
  <TriggerRuleRef name="Cellphone Trigger Attribute Change Rule"/>
</IdentityLifecycleEvent>
Note: Yeh settings aap IIQ UI mein Setup -> Business Processes -> Lifecycle Events mein jaakar direct UI se bhi add kar sakte hain.

3. Identity Refresh Task (Chalu karne ka niyam)
SailPoint mein yeh event automatic tabhi trigger hote hain jab system ko pata chalta hai ki attribute badla hai. Iske liye ek niyam hai:

Jab bhi aap Identity Refresh Task chalate hain, toh us task ke andar ek checkbox hota hai: "Check Identity Trigger Events".

Us checkbox ko hamesha true (checked) rakhna padta hai. Jaise hi Refresh task chalega, woh badle hue users ko dhoodhega, Trigger Rule unhe filter karega, aur Workflow unka email daag dega.

Ek Choti Summary:
Trigger Rule: Parde ke peeche purane aur naye data ko compare karke filter lagata hai.

Lifecycle Event: Rule aur Workflow ka aapas mein rishta jotta hai.

Refresh Task: In sabko har din ya har ghante automatic parde ke peeche chalata hai.

