Ab aapka poora ticket framework complete ho chuka hai, isko ek sath dekhiye:

preApproval → ServiceNow mein ticket khula (Status: New).

postApproval → Manager ne haan bola, ticket update hua (Status: Approved).

Provision → SailPoint ne Active Directory mein user ka account bana diya.

postProvisioning (Yeh wala step) → SailPoint ne ServiceNow ko bola kaam khatam, ticket ko Close kar do (Status: Closed/Completed).

ye workflow custom tha

Aapne bilkul sahi pakda! Yeh ek Custom Subprocess Workflow hai.

Lekin isme ek bahut hi mazaedaar baat hai—yeh poora custom nahi hai, balki isko "OOTB (Out-of-the-Box) aur Custom ka ek smart mix" keh sakte hain. SailPoint ki language mein ise hum Customized Standard Subprocess bolte hain.

Aaiye mai aapko batata hoon ki isme kya cheez standard hai aur kis wajah se yeh custom bana hai:

1. Yeh "Standard" (OOTB) kyun lagta hai?
Is workflow ke andar jo badi-badi logic chal rahi hain, unke liye SailPoint ke standard features ka hi use kiya gaya hai:

Isme use hone wale variables (jaise identityName, plan, approvalScheme) bilkul standard SailPoint LCM framework ke hain.

Jo tasks call ho rahe hain, jaise  aur , yeh SailPoint ke apne pehle se bane-banaye standard engines hain.

2. Toh phir isme "Custom" kya hai? (Aapne kaise pehchana)
Isko kisi developer ne aapki company ki specific requirements ke mutabik design (tailor) kiya hai, kyunki standard SailPoint mein cheezein aisi nahi dikhtin:

Alag se Subprocess Banana: Standard SailPoint mein Approval aur Provisioning aamtaur par ek bade LCM Provisioning workflow ke andar hi chalte hain. Lekin yahan isko kaat kar ek alag chota subprocess banaya gaya hai: name="Approve and Provision Subprocess".

Parallel Item Splitting: Isme ek variable hai approvalSplitPoint. Iska matlab jab ek request mein 5 alag-alag roles maange gaye hon, toh yeh custom workflow un 5 items ko alag-alag todta hai aur unke liye alag-alag parallel approval subprocess chala deta hai. Standard workflow poore plan ko ek sath bhejta hai.

Smart Ticketing Placement: Isme Approve step ke just baad aur Provision step ke just baad ServiceNow/Jira (Manage Ticket) ko call kiya gaya hai. Yeh custom sequencing isliye ki gayi hai taaki external ticket ka status SailPoint ke har ek move ke sath bilkul matching chale.

Ek Line mein Verdict:
Yeh workflow ek Custom-built Gadi ki tarah hai, jiske engine aur purze toh SailPoint ke asli standard hain, lekin iska dashboard, iska rasta (Transition to...), aur iske chalne ka tarika aapke developer ne khud code karke design kiya hai!

