Aaiye aapke in dono sawalon ka ekdam step-by-step jawab samajhte hain ki is Form aur Workflow ko SailPoint mein kahan daalna hai aur ise chalane ke liye kya niyam ya rules hote hain.

1. Yeh Form aur Workflow kahan upload karein?
SailPoint IdentityIQ (IIQ) mein kisi bhi XML file (chahe woh Form ho, Workflow ho, ya Rule) ko upload karne ka ek hi standard tarika hota hai, jise hum "Import" bolte hain.

Upload karne ka tarika (Sequence):
Pehle aap Form XML ka code ek notepad mein save karke uska naam SampleForm.xml rakh lijiye.

Phir Workflow XML ka code save karke uska naam SampleWorkflow.xml rakh lijiye.

SailPoint IIQ ke Console UI par jaaiye aur top menu mein Global Settings (Gears ka icon) par click kirdi-jiye.

Wahan dropdown mein aapko Import from File ka option milega.

Pehle Form ki XML file ko select karke Import button dabaiye, aur uske baad Workflow ki XML file ko select karke Import dabaiye.

Zaroori Baat: Hamesha pehle Form ko import karna, phir Workflow ko. Kyunki agar aapne pehle workflow import kiya, toh SailPoint validation error de dega ki "Bhai, mujhe Sample Workflow Form naam ka form database mein nahi mil raha hai!"

2. Is Workflow ko chalane ka koi Rule bhi hai kya?
Technically, is workflow ko direct chalane ke liye koi Java/BeanShell Rule nahi chahiye hota hai. Lekin isko trigger karne ke liye SailPoint ka ek niyam/setup hota hai jise hum QuickLink Configuration bolte hain.

Aapka sawal tha ki user ka ek "QuickLink hai jo workflow ko trigger karta hai". Toh use chalane ke liye parde ke peeche yeh 3 niyam (Steps) poore hone chahiye:

Niyam A: Ek QuickLink Object Hona Chahiye
Aapko SailPoint mein ek QuickLink object banana padta hai jo dashboard par ek button ke roop mein dikhega. Us QuickLink XML ke andar aapko batana padta hai ki is button ke dabte hi kaun sa workflow chalega.

Uska configuration kuch aisa dikhta hai:

XML
