I have a requirement so that we need to crete a custom object to manage that object into identityiq. matlab

IdentityIQ (IIQ) mein Custom Object banane ka matlab hota hai "SailPoint ke database mein apni ek nayi table (ya data structure) banana".

SailPoint ke paas pehle se kuch standard objects hote hain jaise Identity (users ke liye), Application (target systems ke liye), aur Link (accounts ke liye). Lekin jab aapki company ki koi aisi requirement ho jo in standard objects mein fit nahi baithti, tab hum Custom Object banate hain.

Aaiye isko ekdam simple shabdo aur real-world examples se samajhte hain:

Iska Asli Matlab Kya Hai? (Real-World Examples)
Maan lijiye aapko SailPoint ke andar kuch aisa data store karna hai jiska users ya accounts se seedha lena-dena nahi hai, jaise:

City and Branch Managers List: Aapko ek data table chahiye jisme likha ho ki "Agar city Mumbai hai, toh manager Amit hoga; agar Delhi hai, toh Rahul hoga." Yeh data aap Workflows ya Rules mein check karna chahte hain.

Application Risk Mapping: Ek aisi table jahan har application ke aage uski business criticality likhi ho (e.g., Active Directory = High, Zoom = Low).

Temporary Exclusions: Un employees ki list jinhe agle 2 mahine tak automatic certification se bahar (exclude) rakhna hai.

Yeh saara data store karne ke liye SailPoint mein pehle se koi bani-banayi jagah nahi hoti. Isi tarah ke data ko hold karne ke liye hum ek custom sancha banate hain, jise Custom Object bola jata hai.

Parde ke Peeche Yeh Kaise Kaam Karta Hai?
SailPoint ke database (MySQL/Oracle) mein ek table hoti hai jiska naam hai spt_custom.

Jab aap koi Custom Object banate hain, toh woh isi table ke andar ek Key-Value Pair (Attributes Map) ke roop mein jaakar save ho jata hai. Iska sabse bada fayda yeh hai ki aap pure Java Code (BeanShell) ke zariye is data ko jab chahein padh (get) sakte hain aur badal (update) sakte hain.

Ek Simple Custom Object XML Kaisa Dikhta Hai?
Agar aapko ek custom configuration save karni hai, toh uska XML structure aisa hota hai:

XML
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Custom PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Custom name="MyCompanyCustomConfig">
  <Attributes>
    <Map>
      <!-- Yahan aap apna manchaha data save kar sakte hain -->
      <entry key="MumbaiBranchManager" value="amit.sharma"/>
      <entry key="DelhiBranchManager" value="rahul.verma"/>
      <entry key="MaxAllowedRoles" value="5"/>
    </Map>
  </Attributes>
</Custom>
Code Mein Iska Use Kaise Karte Hain? (Developer Perspective)
Jab aap is Custom Object ko SailPoint mein import kar dete hain, toh aap kisi bhi Rule ya Workflow ke andar isko sirf 2 lines ke code se access kar sakte hain:

Java
import sailpoint.object.Custom;

// 1. Database se custom object ko uske naam se khinch kar lao
Custom config = context.getObjectByName(Custom.class, "MyCompanyCustomConfig");

// 2. Uske andar se koi bhi value nikal lo
String manager = (String) config.get("MumbaiBranchManager"); 
// Result mileyga: "amit.sharma"
