SailPoint standard LCM workflows mein variables ko value milne ke alag-alag tareeqe hote hain. Aapne jo code diya hai, usme bahut saare variables aise hain jinme koi initializer="..." (starting value) ya script nahi likha hai.

Aaiye bilkul saaf aur aasan shabdo mein samajhte hain ki jin variables ke paas koi value nahi dikh rahi hai, unhe asal mein value milti kahan se hai:

1. input="true" wale Variables ko value kaun deta hai?
Aapke code mein jin variables ke aage input="true" likha hai aur koi initializer nahi hai (jaise identityName, plan, flow, ticketManagementApplication, approvingIdentities), unhe value bahar se pass ki jaati hai.

Inhe value dene ke 3 main sources hote hain:

LCM User Interface (UI): Jab koi user ya manager SailPoint ke portal par jaakar koi Naya Access Request submit karta hai, toh SailPoint ka frontend system khud us request se data uthata hai. Jaise:

Jis user ke liye request ki gayi, uska naam identityName mein chala jata hai.

Jo access maanga gaya, uska blueprint plan mein chala jata hai.

Quicklink Configuration: SailPoint UI mein jo buttons hote hain (Manage User Access, View Identity, etc.), unhe "Quicklinks" kehte hain. Un quicklinks ke piche pehle se set hota hai ki jab is button par click hoga, toh flow ki value kya hogi (jaise "AccountsRequest" ya "RolesRequest").

Launch Args (Form Entries): Jab workflow start hota hai, toh SailPoint ka system parde ke peeche ek Map (Key-Value pair) banakar is workflow ko saunp deta hai, jise Launch Arguments kehte hain.

2. Kuch Khaas Variables jinhe runtime par doosre Steps value dete hain
Kuch variables aise hote hain jo shuruat mein poore khali (null) hote hain, lekin workflow ke chalte-chalte beech ke steps unhe bharte hain:

approvalSet: Shuru mein isme koi value nahi hoti. Lekin jab workflow ka ek step chalta hai jiska naam hota hai "Build Approval Set", toh woh step pooray plan ko scan karta hai aur line items banakar is approvalSet variable ke andar daal deta hai.

project: Shuru mein yeh bhi khali hota hai. Jab "Compile Plan" wala step chalta hai, toh woh function apna output nikal kar resultVariable="project" ke zariye isme value bhar deta hai.

policyViolations: Jab shuruat mein SailPoint ka policy check step chalta hai, agar use koi violation milti hai, toh woh is variable ke andar un violations ki list save kar deta hai.

identityRequestId: Jab SailPoint ka system is access request ke liye database mein ek naya ticket number register karta hai, toh woh auto-incremented id (jaise 0000001) is variable mein daal di jaati hai.

3. Ekdam Unique Cases (Blank Variable standard workflow mein)
Aapke code mein kuch variables bilkul blank hain, jaise:
<Variable input="true" name="approvalAssignmentRule"/>
<Variable input="true" name="formTemplate"/>
<Variable input="true" name="manualActionsEmailTemplate"/>

Inka intezaam SailPoint ne aise kiya hai:

System Defaults / Fallback: Agar aapne inme koi value nahi di aur bahar se bhi koi value nahi aayi, toh SailPoint ke back-end code mein pehle se kuch default values tay hoti hain, system unhe use kar leta hai.

Business Process Configuration Page (UI Settings): SailPoint ke admin panel mein ek page hota hai jahan is pooray workflow ki graphical settings dikhti hain. Agar Admin ne wahan UI par koi Custom Rule select kiya hai approval assign karne ke liye, toh SailPoint automatic us rule ka naam is approvalAssignmentRule ke andar daal kar workflow ko bhej deta hai.

Summary Table (Quick Reference)
Variable Name	Isko Value Kaun Deta Hai?	Kab Milti Hai Value?
identityName, plan, flow, source	LCM UI / Requester (Jo access maang raha hai)	Workflow shuru hote hi (At Launch)
approvalSet	"Build Approval Set" Step	Workflow ke chalte waqt beech mein
project	"Compile Project" Step	Workflow ke chalte waqt beech mein
identityRequestId	SailPoint Engine (Database Ticket)	Jaise hi ticket create hota hai
approvalAssignmentRule, formTemplate	Admin UI Settings (Agar admin ne set kiya ho, warna null rehte hain)	Workflow shuru hote hi
