preApproval vs postApproval me antar kya hai

preApproval aur postApproval dono SailPoint IdentityIQ mein ticketing system (jaise ServiceNow ya Jira) ko bheje jaane wale Commands (Actions) hain. Inka sabse bada antar yeh hai ki yeh ticket ke life-cycle mein kab aur kya kaam karte hain.

Aaiye inka antar ekdam saaf aur simple shabdo mein samajhte hain:

1. Timing ka Antar (Kab chalte hain?)
preApproval (Approval se Pehle): Yeh tab chalta hai jab kisi employee ne access request just submit ki ho aur abhi tak Manager ya Owner ke paas approval ka notification gaya bhi na ho.

postApproval (Approval ke Baad): Yeh tab chalta hai jab Manager ya Approver ne request ko check karke "Approve" (haan) ya "Reject" (naa) ka button daba diya ho.

2. Kaam ka Antar (Kya karte hain?)
Swabhav (Feature)	preApproval	postApproval
Main Target	ServiceNow mein ek Naya Ticket Paida (Create) karna.	Purane bane hue ticket ko Update karna.
Ticket Status	Ticket ka status "New", "Submitted", ya "Pending Approval" set karta hai.	Ticket ka status badal kar "Approved" ya "Work In Progress" set karta hai.
Data (Information)	Isme bataya jata hai ki request kisne dali hai aur kya access maanga hai.	Isme manager ka final decision aur uske likhe hue Comments/Remarks ticket mein daale jaate hain.
Maqsad (Goal)	IT Helpdesk ko batana ki ek nayi request system mein aayi hai (Tracking shuru karna).	IT Helpdesk ko batana ki manager ne haan bol diya hai, ab access dene ki taiyari karo.
