1. Duplicate Hierarchy Ki Galti (Aasan Bhasha Mein)
SailPoint ke Form Engine ka ek strict rule hota hai: Ek pita (Parent) ke andar hi bacha (Child) baith sakta hai, aur ek bacha ek hi waqt par do alag-alag pitaon ka direct child nahi ho sakta.

User ne code mein kya kiya, is hierarchy (family tree) se dekhiye:

Sahi Tarika (Standard):
Form → contains → Section → contains → Field (fv)
(Yaani field, section ka bacha hai; aur section, form ka bacha hai).

User ki Galti:
User ne pehle likha: sects.add(fv); (Field chala gaya Section ke andar).
Phir likha: forms.add(sects); (Section chala gaya Form ke andar).
Aur phir galti se ye line likh di: forms.add(fv);

Is aakhiri line ki wajah se SailPoint ka engine confuse ho gaya kyunki ab fv (Field) direct Form ke andar bhi baithne ki koshish kar raha hai aur Section ke andar bhi. Jab SailPoint iska XML convert karne jata hai, toh structure corrupt ho jata hai aur UI crash ho jata hai. Logs mein error isliye nahi aati kyunki Java ke mutabik object creation sahi hai, par SailPoint ka UI processor ise padh nahi paata.

2. Poora Working Custom Workflow XML
Yeh raha aapka full-proof solution. Isme humne us Java code ko ekdam clean karke Workflow ke step ke andar direct set kar diya hai. Yeh bina kisi alag Form file ke, dynamic tarike se 'n' number of fields generate karega.

XML
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Workflow PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Workflow explicitTransitions="true" name="Dynamic QuickLink Form Workflow" type="IdentityLifecycle">

  <!-- Core Variables -->
  <Variable input="true" name="identityName">
    <Description>The name of the identity triggering the QuickLink.</Description>
  </Variable>
  <Variable input="true" name="launcher">
    <Description>The person who clicked the QuickLink.</Description>
  </Variable>

  <!-- STEP 1: START -->
  <Step icon="Start" name="Start" posX="28" posY="10">
    <Transition to="Generate and Display Form Step"/>
  </Step>

  <!-- STEP 2: DYNAMIC FORM GENERATION & DISPLAY -->
  <Step icon="Approval" name="Generate and Display Form Step" posX="150" posY="10">
    <Approval owner="ref:launcher" return="driveAction">
      <Arg name="workItemType" value="Form"/>
      <Arg name="workItemDescription" value="Please fill out the dynamically generated questionnaire."/>
      
      <!-- Script jo situation ke hisab se 'n' fields generate karega -->
      <Script>
        <Source>
          import sailpoint.object.Form;
          import sailpoint.object.Form.Section;
          import sailpoint.object.Form.Field;
          import sailpoint.object.Form.Button;
          import java.util.ArrayList;

          // 1. Naya Custom Form banayein
          Form dynamicForm = new Form();
          dynamicForm.setPageTitle("Dynamic Request Portal");

          // 2. Section banayein (Fields ko hold karne ke liye)
          Form.Section section = new Form.Section();
          section.setName("dynamicSection");
          section.setLabel("Dynamic Input Fields");
          
          // 3. Dynamic Loop Logic ('n' number of fields)
          // Yahan '3' ki jagah aap company ki requirement ya kisi list ka size le sakte hain
          int n = 3; 
          for (int i = 1; i &lt;= n; i++) {
              Form.Field fv = new Form.Field();
              fv.setName("dynamicField_" + i);
              fv.setLabel("Dynamic Field Number " + i);
              fv.setType("string"); // Sahi type lowercase 'string' hota hai
              fv.setRequired(true);
              
              // Sahi Tarika: Field ko sirf aur sirf Section mein add karein
              section.add(fv); 
          }

          // 4. Section ko Form mein dalein
          dynamicForm.add(section);

          // 5. Next aur Back Buttons lagayein
          Form.Button nextBtn = new Form.Button();
          nextBtn.setAction("next");
          nextBtn.setLabel("Submit Request");
          
          ArrayList btnList = new ArrayList();
          btnList.add(nextBtn);
          dynamicForm.setButtons(btnList);

          // Pura bana hua form SailPoint UI ko return kar dein
          return dynamicForm;
        </Source>
